<div class="blog-header-left">
  <h1>
    <a href="/blog/brain-sense">Brain Sense</a>  </h1>
  <div class="blog-header-description">
    How your brain makes sense of your senses.  </div>
  <div class="blog-header-byline">
    by Faith Brynie  </div>
</div>
</div>
					</div>
								<div id="content-content">
				  
<div id="node-55574" class="node node-article clear-block seq-1">
	
    <div class="page-title">
      <h1>Sleep Helps Us Remember What We Need To</h1>
    </div>

  	
  	<div class="article-abstract">
      Expectation "tags" memories for consolidation during sleep.  	</div>
  	<div class="article-meta">
  	 	        <span class="submitted">Published on February 18, 2011 by <a href="/experts/faith-brynie-phd" title="View Bio">Faith Brynie, Ph.D.</a> in <a href="/blog/brain-sense">Brain Sense</a></span>
        	</div> 	
		
    <div class="content">
      <div class="article-content-top">
        <a href="/basics/pornography" title="Psychology Today looks at Pornography" class="pt-basics-link"> </a><p><div class="article-image-wrap article-image-wrap-article-inline-half" style="width: 230px;"><img src="http://rsrc.psychologytoday.com/files/imagecache/article-inline-half/blogs/32058/2011/02/55574-47627.jpg" alt="" title="" /></div><a href="/basics/sleep" title="Psychology Today looks at Sleep" class="pt-basics-link">Sleep</a> Helps Us Remember What We Need To.</p><p>The jury is back and the verdict is in. The long-term storage of <a href="/basics/memory" title="Psychology Today looks at Memory" class="pt-basics-link">memories</a> occurs during sleep. It's not just&nbsp;a passive process of forgetting--in which useless or trivial short-term memories fade into obscurity. Memory storage during sleep is an active process. Several researchers have shown that neuronal representations of memories are reactivated during sleep, as if the <a href="/basics/neuroscience" title="Psychology Today looks at Neuroscience" class="pt-basics-link">brain</a> were replaying a recording. The replay is essential to long-term memory storage, possibly because it redistributes neuronal connections from short-term memory to long-term storage sites in the neocortex.</p>      </div>
      <div id="inline-content-bottom-left">
          <div id="block-blog_post_collection" class="block">
    	<div class="pt-box ">
  													<div class="pt-box-title">
									<h2>
										See All Stories In									  									</h2>
							</div>
															<div class="pt-box-content">
															
															
																<div class="view-primary">
																			<div class="view-content">
											<div class="post-in-collection-image"><img src="http://rsrc.psychologytoday.com/files/imagecache/collections-home-thumb/collections/2010/12/51952-73101.jpg" alt="" title=""  class="imagecache imagecache-collections-home-thumb" width="142" height="83" /></div><h2><a href="/collections/201201/the-top-50-posts-2011" style="text-decoration: underline; ">The Top 50 Posts of 2011</a></h2><p>We want to be liked and we want to laugh. Posts that caught fire last year. </p>										</div>
																	</div>
							
								
															
															
														</div>
				</div>
</div>
  <div class='advertisement advertisement-zone-51'>
